Very intense met-con with two classic CF movements. If 225 DU is to much maybe do a combination of DUs and Singel unders but don´t settle for the easy way out.

Workout.name: Filthy fifty
Workout.description:
For Time;
50 Box Jumps/Step ups 60/50 cm
50 Jumping Pull-Ups
50 Kettlebell Swings american 16/12 kg or individual weight
50 Walking Lunge Steps
50 Knees-to-Elbows/Knee-raises
50 Push Presses 20/15 kg or individual weight
50 Back Extensions in the GHD/50 Barbell goodmornings 20/15 kg
50 Wall Ball Shots 9/6 kg 3/2,7 m
50 Burpees
50 Double-Unders/Singel unders 2 for 1 Double under
Time cap 35 min

The Filthy fifty is a classic CrossFit benchmark workout that can be very hard if your going all out. If this is your first workout of many this week it´s recommended to stay back on the pace and break up or slow down on all of the movements. 

The correct height for the Jumping pull-ups is 5 to 10 cm below the wrist. 

To accommodate the workout in a class setting the movements can be performed in any order.

15 Box Jump Overs 60/50 cm or lower

The exact standards can be read here; https://games.crossfit.com/workouts/open/2022/1
For training thou touching the chest or nose to the wall without arching the back is a good standard. 
Find your own sustainable pace from the start and if possible finish strong the last two minutes.

Workout.name: 2K Rowing
Workout.description:
2K Row for time is a very good measurement of your absolute aerobic capacity. 
This means you have to pace yourself somewhat from the beginning to stay just below the lactic threshold and then finish strong.

8 - 6 - 4 - 2 Thrusters. Build weight 60% of 1 RM and start from the floor with a Power clean
2 - 4 Hamstring walk outs

Tips: thrusters: think slow slow and when close to the mid-tights, explose hips, nearly like jumping up

10-12 Alternating v-ups
5 - 7 + 5 - 7 Skater squats for quality
rest 1 min

or

1 min Hang from the bar. Try different grips supinated, mix grip and also small swings back and forth or sideways. 
3 min Singel unders two feet, run, one foot etc. Mix it up!
1 min Front leaning rest in the rings/Floor. Best possible hollow "gymnasty" position!

Endurance session which will be strengthening the central capacity (heart and lungs) and also the muscular upper body isometric endurance. Maybe try nose breathing on the conditioning movements.

Workout.name: 1RM Thruster (open 23.2B)
Workout.description:
Straight from 23.2A (amrap 15min)

5 minutes to Establish:
1 rep max Thruster

——
Indications
Immediately after the conclusion of 23.2A (15 minutes), a 5-minute timer begins for 23.2B. Athletes have 5 minutes to complete their best 1-rep-max Thruster. Athletes may make as many attempts as they’d like within the 5-minute time cap and may have assistance loading the Barbell between attempts. Any successful attempt where the Bar leaves the ground before the 5-minute time cap will count.

Score for 23.2B will be the heaviest successful lift (in pounds).

5, 5, 5, 5, 4, 4, 4, 4, 3, 3, 3, 3  minute on 4 machines for a total of 48 minutes.
For instance start at the Rower for 5 minutes, continue on the Treadmill for 5 minutes, continue to the Bike for 5 minutes and then finish on the Ski erg for 5 minutes. Next round you will go in the same order of machines but only for 4 minutes on each. And the last round it will be 3 minutes on each machine.

Workout.name: Open 23.2A
Workout.description:
AMRAP in 15 minutes
5 Burpee Pull-Ups*
10 Shuttle Runs (25 ft out, 25 ft back)

*Add 5 Burpee Pull-Ups after each round (5 bp, run, 10 bp, run…)

Then STRAIGHT INTO 23.2B

Scaling: 
AMRAP in 15 minutes
5 Burpees to target (jump to touch the bar)
10 Shuttle Runs (25 ft out, 25 ft back)
*Add 5 Burpees after each round

——
Tips: https://wodprep.com/blog/23-2-open-strategies-scaled-masters-athletes/
——
Indications:
Prior to starting the test, follow the instructions in the movement standards for the Burpee Pull-Up to find a Pull-Up Bar of appropriate height. Then create a Shuttle Run measuring 25 ft. The Pull-Up Bar may be in any configuration as long as the athlete starts each shuttle run behind the designated shuttle-run start line. At the conclusion of 23.2A, barbells can be moved or placed as needed to complete 23.2B. Barbells may start pre-loaded to any weight.

Test 23.2A begins on the far side of the Shuttle Run, furthest from the Pull-Up Bar. At the sound of the beep, run to the other side of the Shuttle Run and begin the first set of Burpee Pull-Ups. After completing 5 reps, complete 10 Shuttle Runs. One Shuttle Run = 50 ft (25 ft down the field of play and 25 ft back).

After the Shuttle Runs, return to the Pull-Up bar and complete 10 Burpee Pull-Ups and 10 Shuttle Runs. Then complete 15 Burpee Pull-Ups and 10 Shuttle Runs. Continue in this fashion, adding 5 Burpee Pull-Ups after each set of 10 Shuttle Runs until the 15-minute time cap.

Score for 23.2A will be the total number of repetitions completed by the 15-minute time cap.

Immediately after the conclusion of 23.2A (15 minutes), a 5-minute timer begins for 23.2B.

Doing the 10x500m correctly is crucial – lets bullet point these, just so there is nothing left unclear:

- Take is easier in the first 5-6 500s and aim to build for the last 4-5.
- Do not go too hard too early – this is a major mistake and you will pay for it later in the session.
-Attack the first 5 strokes to get your average split down (use short strokes for 1-2 then lengthen)
- Relax. Yes – work hard on the power phase, but relax on the recovery.
- Keep moving very slowly and pulling very light on the rest phase.

Result is the total time

Workout.name: Team Bear complex
Workout.description:
In 15 min individually Build up to a 3 RM "broken" Bear complex
Broken means stopping after each movement I.e.power clean - front squat - jerk - back squat - jerk (=1 rep). The barbell can not rest on the floor thou.
Start light (60% of 1 RM Clean and Jerk) and build from there over 5 - 6 sets.

How to Calculate Zone 2

- Heart Rate Reerve (HRR) = 220 - You Age- Resting Heart Rate (RHR)
- Zone 2 Range:
Minimum = RHR + .5 (HRR)
Maximum = RHR + .75 (HRR)

-Example: for 30 year Old with 60 Resting Heart Rate
RHR = 220 -30 -60 = 130

Zone 2 Range
Minimum = 60 + .5 (130) = 60 + 65 = 125
Maximum = 60 + .75(130 = 60 + 98 = 148

Zone 2 Range = 125 bpm to 148 bpm

1.        ~ 30-50%        8 reps

3.        ~ 70%        3        at ~ 4 minutes
4.        ~ 80%        1        at ~ 7 minutes
